  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1703632" />
    <a title="Lynne Wald" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/118818-lynne-wald"><img alt="Lynne Wald" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1181107044p2/118818.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1703632?book_show_action=true">Jun 06, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lynne Wald" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lynne Wald" href="/user/show/118818-lynne-wald">Lynne Wald</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">TOTALLY</span></div>

        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1703632" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14643193228915473746">This is one of my favourite books of all time. The writing is fantastic, the characters so well penned that I came to care about them, and when I put the book down, I wanted to continue to know these people, which to me is a good indication that the book is top notch. Scotland came to life for me here, and I really wanted to go there at christmas time and experience Scotland at that period. I have read it several times and will continue to pick it up on occasions.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


